<dl id="n35215c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35215c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35215c"> 215(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Shear the hair</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>The Ceremonies and Merwa</i>.&mdash; [&hellip;]</font> at Taif, for example, it was customary on return to the city after an abscence to present oneself at the sancttuary, and there shear the hair. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
